			<tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">In the 56 Levels that I have achieved in playing IMHO the best class ever. I wanted to share some little tips and tactics that people can either use, not use or improve upon:
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Agro</span>
<br />
“Min and Max Melee range is a myth created by warriors who are so bored playing their class that they have to make stuff up to do something to relieve the monotony.” Well really there is Max and Min Melee range but with all the bouncing around that happens to a mob it does not make much of a difference. My favourite of all time was when a mate of mine who I have been grouping with for 2 years asked me to move my Warder back to max melee range as it was stealing his agro (man was he having a bad day) /pet max melee.
<br />

<br />
Nothing agros a mob better than slow EXCEPT:
<br />
1. Casting a de-buff directly after it.
<br />
2. Casting another slow.
<br />
3. Sitting down after any of the above. YES SIT DOWN AGRO or SDO as I will call it is a fantastically useful tool. Mob too far away because your warder went rabid when the mob got a lucky hit in on you??? Well cast slow again (more than likely used this to pull) and/or de-buff and then sit. The mob will usually move up to you.
<br />

<br />
Great for placement of mobs. I am sometimes forced to do this when the puller or Main Tank decides it would be a good idea to fight in the middle of add central. 
<br />

<br />
I don’t have Spirit of the Storm or Flame so I cant test whether this can or cant be used as a sort of reverse fear kite. Hopefully someone will respond to my post with this information.
<br />

<br />
Sitting down creates major agro as outlined above, but sitting whilst a pull is in progress in high level zones will get you killed. I have been forced to use this technique to save AFK casters on raids in the Umbral Plains.
<br />

<br />
Watch for Low Hitpoint Agro in high level zones like Umbral Planes and Planes of Power. Mobs love to kill weaker opponents off first.
<br />

<br />
If a tank is losing agro to you and then starts blaming you for it you can either:
<br />
1. Tell him that you are playing the second most damaging class in the game and that it is only natural that you are getting agro from him (and then seem like an uber arrogant person)
<br />

<br />
OR
<br />

<br />
2. Tell him that he should be using a faster weapon and/or maybe two of them to get more agro. A weapon that procs something or even hitting the taunt key might help.
<br />

<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Flash of Light</span> is one of the most useful spell that you can ever get (Warder excluded of course) and here is why:
<br />
1. You can pull with it at low level. This is because you don’t get an ranged attack spells till much later.
<br />
2. You can fear kite with it by casting it, moving out of range of mob, telling pet to back off and then sitting (well that’s what I do anyway). I used this technique at great lengths on Gornit in the Ocean of Tears (cash cow) so that I could kill him more easily and to scare the heck out of people in the boat that went past.
<br />
3. In PvP it rocks.
<br />
4. It also (certainly at low levels) is a great way of increasing damage you and your pet do. I even use it now at 56th level. Every little bit helps.
<br />
5. Last but by no means the least. It gets rid of adds. But remember the mob add that is running it’s butt off to god knows where will most likely return with buddies.
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">Kodiac’s Endless Intellect</span> is your friend but DON’T rely on it. There will be a situation where you wont have it and you will overestimate what you have. You will be glad to know that there are some institutions in Norrath that can help you to detox, councillors there can and will assist your recovery.
<br />

<br />
Never zone into the Swamp of No Hope from Trakanon’s Teeth without due caution and diligence. My favourite mob lives there. Go there one day. See them and suffer as many have done to the “Death of a Thousand Nibbles”. &lt;Had to put this one in for comic relief and all those lowbie Iksar out there&gt;
<br />

<br />
<span style="font-weight: bold">DONT DIE</span>. Best piece of advice I can offer.
<br />

<br />
As time goes by I may add more to this but I just wanted some feedback at the moment. I have not put in the simple ones like:
<br />
·A dropped Sword points North.
<br />
·Clouds travel from East to West.
<br />
·Etc etc
<br />

<br />
But was wondering if I should. Please let me know.
<br />

<br />
Regards
<br />
Churon Deathbringer – Recovering KEI addict.</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
			</tr>
		</table></td>
	</tr>
