				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">FWIW on many enounters, "max melee" is the diff between a win, and a raidwipe.  Now, if you (your raid) can't balance a mob when you have to, that is another set of problems <img src="images/smiles/icon_smile.gif" alt="Smile" border="0" />
<br />

<br />
And tell yer buddy that pet always attacks at max range - if he seems close sometimes, it's becuse the mob has a small hitbox.  Had a raid leader yell over the raid channel on an AoW mauling "If you are in front of the stupid tiger BACK UP!"  
<br />

<br />
I rarely use my pet on raids (my choice, not by decree) but when I do it is usually for one of 2 reasons - to set my max range, or in places with tons of mezzed adds, I /assist the MA (or F8 if I am MA) and send the pet - then follow the pet to the proper target.  Saves a lot of those "you cant see your target" "you are too damn far away" messages.
<br />

<br />
Speaking of not balancing mobs, when it is not critical we just flat suck. "The Treelentless" we have dubbed ourselves. I think there are a couple of pics on our news page if you get around to looking. The one that is not there yet is from last week when we screwed up something fierce, and pushed Xegony....on top of the only damn tree in PoA.<br />_________________<br /><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=87433" target="_blank" class="postlink"> Ghoat!</a>
