   Just to avoid spreading any more misinformation.  NO, PETS DO NOT HAVE "NATURAL" AGRO.   In other words, mobs will not attack any regular pet unless it is by AoE or the pet's / warder's owner tells it to attack.  It has been this way over almost a year now.<br />_________________<br /><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=67241">Baron Kaatt</A>, Sixty-One Year Old Khati Sha Savage Lord of Xev.<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=337255">Investigator Aaeorn</A>, Fiftieth Circle Redeemed Thief Catcher of Xev.<BR><A HREF="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=362220">Aaeorm</A>, Enchantement Technician of the Thirty-Second Tier of Xev.<BR>Proud member of <A HREF="http://www.eqdissonance.com">Dissonance</A><BR></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
