				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Distance does effect aggro, its more noticable when pulling than meleeing in most cases though.
<br />

<br />
If a warrior looses aggro he should be slamming, begging and taunting the mob. In that order if hes on top of aggro list, reverse order if he lost aggro atm.
<br />

<br />
Sitting will make you count as a L1 - thus the extra aggro, and thats why you loose the extra aggro as soon as you stand.
<br />

<br />
Death aggro will make it impossible to get mobs away from you unless they are feared, rooted, charmed or mezzed.<br />_________________<br /><center><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=360803" target="_blank" OnClick="javascript:window.open('http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=360803','','width=800,height=600'); return false"><img src="http://home.swipnet.se/Nulli-Secundis/pics/DahkarET.jpg" border="0" alt="Click here to inspect"></a></center></span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
